sense.name: tree insides
sense.commentary: the hard fibrous lignified substance under the bark of trees
sense.examples: I prefer furniture that is made of wood. George tripped on his way to get wood for the fire.

sense.name: forest
sense.commentary: the trees and other plants in a large densely wooded area
sense.examples: The children like to go out and play in the woods all day. The teenagers drink in the woods at night.

sense.name: woodwind
sense.commentary: woodwind instrument - any wind instrument other than the brass instruments
sense.examples: This is the part of the song where the woods come in. She plays a wood. I love the sound of the woods.

sense.name: golf club
sense.commentary: a golf club with a long shaft used to hit long shots
sense.examples: Woods were originally made with a wooden head. Metal woods are now available and widely used.

sense.name: Ms. Natalie Wood
sense.commentary: Natalie Wood - United States film actress (1938 - 1981)
sense.examples: I'm a big fan of Wood. Wood was a great actress.

sense.name: Sir Henry Joseph Wood
sense.examples: I'm a big fan of Wood. Wood was an English conductor.

sense.name: Ellen Price Wood
sense.commentary: Mrs. Henry Wood - English writer of novels about murders and thefts and forgeries (1814 - 1887)
sense.examples: I'm a big fan of Wood. Wood was a great writer.

sense.name: Mr. Grant Wood
sense.commentary: United States painter noted for works based on life in the Midwest (1892 - 1887)
sense.examples: Wood was a great painter. I'm a big fan of Wood.
